<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4033.1.5>
    bibo:endPage "116" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "103" ;
    bibo:volume "4033" ;
    dc:creator "Shea, Glenn M." ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "A new species of Anilios (Scolecophidia: Typhlopidae) from Central Australia" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245555>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245551>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245554> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245555>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Headshields of A. wiedii (AM R 162454) for comparison with A. fossor. Note the smaller, narrower, less rounded rostral, the noticeably squarer snout in dorsal profile, and the extension of the nasal cleft onto the head dorsum. Scale bar = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245555/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245551>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Holotype of Anilios fossor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245551/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245554>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Distribution of A. fossor (triangle) within the Northern Territory. The nearest major settlement (Alice Springs) is marked by a square. Relief is indicated by grey shading—pale shading marks higher elevations. Northern Territory borders are 129 ° and 138 ° E and 26 ° S." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245554/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

